    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Oh, you are absolutely right! I was so busy trying to make the goblins dance that I forgot to actually explain the math! 🎺🎺🎺\n\nLet's strip away the goblins and talk about the actual numbers and intervals. The Circle of Fifths is just a map of the **12 semitones** (half steps) in a major scale.\n\nHere is the actual math:\n1.  **The Scale:** A major scale has 7 notes.\n2.  **The Intervals:** The distance between any two adjacent notes in a major scale is exactly a **Major 3rd**.\n3.  **The Math:** A Major 3rd is **4 semitones** (or 2 half steps) away.\n    *   *Example:* From C to E is 4 steps up (C-D-E-F#-G).\n    *   *Example:* From G to C is 4 steps up (G-A-B-C).\n\n**How to use it (The Math Method):**\nTo find the key of a song, you don't need to memorize the whole wheel. You just need to count the **semitones**",
      "source": "target",
